    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="240"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–1145: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 240<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-11">July 11,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. Recommendation that we request British concurrence in our intention, if and
                    when <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName> declares war against <persName
                        corresp="#p_J1">Japan</persName>, to support officially and publicly
                        <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName>’s admission in due course to
                    world security organization is now before the President in papers prepared for
                    Big Three meeting (See <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName>: Topics on
                    Which Discussion is Desired; III, Participation in World Organizations<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d240fn1">
                        <ref target="#d235">Document No. 235</ref>.</note>). Inasmuch as it now
                    appears that <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName> may declare war before
                    Big Three meeting, and since effective value of American action both in US and
                    abroad may depend to great extent upon prompt announcement thereof following
                    Italian declaration, it is believed that we should proceed immediately with
                    recommendation.</p>
                <pb facs="0435" n="303" xml:id="pg_303"/>
                <p>If you agree, and President approves, instructions will be sent <persName
                        corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName> to inform British Government and inquire
                    if it is prepared to support American position.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
